ence can support a scheduled break in studies?","options":["An academic calendar or school letter confirming the break","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Official school evidence can show the break was scheduled and acceptable."},{"level":2,"question":"What can happen if completion evidence is incomplete?","options":["IRCC may request more information or refuse if eligibility is not proven","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The applicant must prove that all PGWP requirements are met."},{"level":2,"question":"Why should identity details match across PGWP documents?","options":["Consistency reduces avoidable concerns about the applicant''s record","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Names and dates of birth should align or be explained with evidence."},{"level":2,"question":"What fees are commonly associated with a PGWP application?","options":["Work permit processing and open work permit holder fees","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"PGWP applicants generally pay both required work permit fees."},{"level":2,"question":"What should a student document after changing schools?","options":["The transfer, study history, and final program eligibility","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Transfers can affect records, timelines, and eligibility analysis."},{"level":2,"question":"How can two eligible one-year programs affect PGWP length?","options":["They may be combined for a longer PGWP if policy conditions are met","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An emp