t does LMIA-exempt mean?","options":["A work permit may be issued under a specific exemption code without an LMIA","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"LMIA-exempt does not necessarily mean work-permit exempt."},{"level":1,"question":"Who usually applies for an LMIA?","options":["The Canadian employer","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Employers apply to ESDC/Service Canada before the worker applies for the permit."},{"level":1,"question":"What supports a worker''s application after a positive LMIA?","options":["LMIA approval and employment offer details","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The worker uses the LMIA and offer documents to support the permit request."},{"level":1,"question":"What is an open work permit?","options":["A permit not tied to one specific employer","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Open permits allow work for most employers, subject to conditions."},{"level":1,"question":"What is a typical closed-permit condition?","options":["Work only for the employer named on the permit","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Working outside listed conditions can create compliance problems."},{"level":1,"question":"What does TFWP stand for?","options":["Temporary Foreign Worker Program","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"TFWP refers to LMIA-based temporary foreign worker hiring."},{"level":1,"question":"Who issues most work permits?","options":["Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"IRCC issues work permits while ESDC assesses LMIAs."},{"level":1,"question":"Who assesses most LMIA applications?","options":["Employment and Social Development Canada or Service Canada","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"ESDC/Service Canada reviews labour market factors."},{"level":1,"question":"Which category can be LMIA-exempt?","options":["Some intra-company transferees","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Certain ICT cases may qualify under IMP rules if criteria are met."},{"level":1,"question":"What is a job offer''s role?","options":["It describes the proposed employment position and conditions","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Work permit applications often rely on detailed employment terms."},{"level":1,"question":"What is the employer compliance fee linked to?","options":["Many LMIA-exempt employer-specific IMP offers","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Employers often submit the offer and pay a fee through the Employer Portal."},{"level":1,"question":"Which portal is used for many LMIA-exempt offers?","options":["Employer Portal","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The Employer Portal links the offer to the worker''s application."},{"level":1,"question":"What does a foreign worker usually need before starting work?","options":["Authorization to work","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Foreign nationals generally need work authorization unless an exemption applies."},{"level":1,"question":"What is not a work permit by itself?","options":["A job offer letter","A regular 