IA is usually needed before the worker''s application."},{"level":3,"question":"What is the risk of working for a different employer on a closed permit?","options":["Unauthorized work and future admissibility concerns","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Closed permits authorize only the listed employment."},{"level":3,"question":"Why can employer compliance history affect future hiring?","options":["Non-compliant employers may face bans, penalties, or refusal risk","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Program compliance findings can affect future foreign-worker hiring."},{"level":3,"question":"What is the issue with paying less than the approved wage?","options":["It may breach employer obligations and permit conditions","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Employers must generally provide the approved wages and conditions."},{"level":3,"question":"When is a duty change problematic?","options":["When duties no longer match the approved NOC or offer","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Material duty changes can require a new assessment."},{"level":3,"question":"Why is NOC misclassification risky?","options":["It can undermine LMIA, work permit, and later PR claims","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"NOC affects eligibility, wages, duties, and immigration alignment."},{"level":3,"question":"What is a risk in owner-operator style LMIA cases?","options":["Questions about genuineness, control, and labour market need","A regular visitor record","A provincial health card","A permanent resident visa"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Ownership-linked employment requires careful evidence.