s · Relationship documents · Funds and admissibility evidence"},{"label":"Rule sensitivity","value":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules.","warning":true},{"label":"Key authority","value":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"label":"After approval","value":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."}],"eligibility":[{"criterion":"Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway","met":true},{"criterion":"Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules","met":true},{"criterion":"Relationship is genuine and well documented","met":true,"note":"Marriage certificate alone may not be enough"},{"criterion":"Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required","met":true},{"criterion":"Principal student program and institution qualify where required","met":true},{"criterion":"Applicant passport valid for requested permit period","met":true},{"criterion":"Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue","met":true},{"criterion":"Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay","met":true},{"criterion":"Medical exam or biometrics completed if required","met":false}],"redFlagsBanner":"Most weak spouse/dependent OWP files fail because the principal applicant does not qualify, the relationship proof is thin, or prior refusals are not addressed.","redFlags":[{"title":"Principal applicant not eligible","description":"Principal worker, student, or PR applicant category does not support dependant OWP.","fix":"Verify current IRCC category before taking full file; assess visitor or other status options","severity":"High"},{"title":"Weak relationship proof","description":"Marriage certificate only, limited photos, no communication, or no shared life evidence.","fix":"Add relationship timeline, photos, chats, travel, financial, and family evidence","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"Recent marriage before filing","description":"Marriage occurred shortly before application with limited relationship history.","fix":"Prepare detailed relationship narrative and third-party corroboration","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Prior refusals not disclosed","description":"Applicant or principal has previous Canada or other country refusals omitted from forms.","fix":"Disclose all refusals and address changed circumstances","severity":"High"},{"title":"Principal status expiring soon","description":"Principal permit expires shortly, limiting dependant permit duration or eligibility.","fix":"Coordinate principal extension or wait for renewed status where strategic","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Insufficient funds","description":"Family cannot show credible support for living costs in Canada.","fix":"Add bank history, employment income, pay stubs, and sponsor explanation","severity":"Medium"},{"title":"Inconsistent forms","description":"Dates, addresses, marital status, or family details conflict across forms.","fix":"Run consistency review against passport, marriage, and prior applications","severity":"Common"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can every spouse of a student get an open work permit?","a":"No. Eligibility depends on current IRCC rules, the student''s program and institution, and other conditions."},{"q":"Can every spouse of a worker get an open work permit?","a":"No. The principal worker''s occupation, permit type, and status must qualify under current policy."},{"q":"Is a marriage certificate enough?","a":"Usually not by itself. Provide relationship history, photos, communication, travel, financial ties, and family evidence where available."},{"q":"Can common-law partners apply?","a":"Yes, if they meet IRCC''s common-law definition and can prove cohabitation and genuine relationship."},{"q":"Can dependent children get open work permits?","a":"Only in limited circumstances. Many children need visitor or study status instead. Screen age and dependency rules carefully."},{"q":"Should the application be filed together with the principal applicant?","a":"Sometimes. It depends on timing, principal eligibility, documents, and risk. Joint filing can help context but is not always best."},{"q":"How long will the OWP be valid?","a":"Often tied to the principal applicant''s status and passport validity. IRCC decides the final duration."},{"q":"Can the applicant work while waiting?","a":"Only if they already have authorization and meet maintained status rules. Outside-Canada applicants cannot work until approved and admitted with proper status."},{"q":"What if there was a previous spouse OWP refusal?","a":"Order notes if useful, address refusal reasons directly, and strengthen principal eligibility and relationship evidence."},{"q":"Does approval lead to PR?","a":"No. OWP is temporary status. It may support Canadian work experience, but PR requires a separate pathway."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Open work permit pathway for eligible spouses, common-law partners, or qualifying dependants linked to a principal applicant''s Canadian work, study, or immigration status."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Genuine spouse/common-law partner or eligible dependant · Principal applicant has qualifying status · Relationship documents · Funds and admissibility evidence"},{"q":"What is Rule sensitivity for this service?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"Important note on Rule sensitivity?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."},{"q":"Is Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway required?","a":"Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules required?","a":"Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules is typically required."},{"q":"Is Relationship is genuine and well documented required?","a":"Marriage certificate alone may not be enough"},{"q":"Is Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required required?","a":"Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Principal student program and institution qualify where required required?","a":"Principal student program and institution qualify where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant passport valid for requested permit period required?","a":"Applicant passport valid for requested permit period is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue required?","a":"Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue is typically required."},{"q":"Is Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay required?","a":"Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay is typically required."},{"q":"Is Medical exam or biometrics completed if required required?","a":"Assess whether Medical exam or biometrics completed if required is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"3–5m — Varies by applicant location"},