CC — Pay your fees","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/application/pay-fees.html","description":"Current work permit and open work permit holder fees"}],"quiz":[{"level":1,"question":"What is a spouse or dependent open work permit?","options":["An open work permit for an eligible spouse or partner of a qualifying worker or student","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The permit can allow the spouse or partner to work for most employers."},{"level":1,"question":"What is the key advantage of an open work permit?","options":["It is not tied to one named employer","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Open permits provide labour-market flexibility subject to conditions."},{"level":1,"question":"Which relationship is commonly relevant?","options":["Spouse or common-law partner","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Eligibility usually depends on a genuine qualifying relationship."},{"level":1,"question":"Can dependent children always get open work permits through this category?","options":["No, children''s options depend on age, status, and program rules","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Dependent children may need visitor, study, or other authorization depending on facts."},{"level":1,"question":"What does C41 commonly relate to?","options":["Spouses of certain skilled workers","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"C41 has been used for spouse open work permit eligibility connected to skilled workers."},{"level":1,"question":"What does C42 commonly relate to?","options":["Spouses of certain international students","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"C42 has been used for spouse open work permits connected to qualifying students."},{"level":1,"question":"Does an open work permit guarantee entry to Canada?","options":["No, entry is still assessed separately","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A permit approval does not remove admissibility or border assessment."},{"level":1,"question":"Who issues spouse open work permits?","options":["Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"IRCC assesses and issues work permits."},{"level":1,"question":"What must the principal worker or student usually have?","options":["Valid status and qualifying work or study circumstances","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The spouse''s eligibility depends on the principal applicant''s qualifying situation."},{"level":1,"question":"Which document proves marriage?","options":["Marriage certificate","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Civil status documents help prove the spousal relationship."},{"level":1,"question":"How is common-law partnership usually shown?","options":["Cohabitation and shared-life evidence for the required period","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Common-law cases need evidence beyond a simple statement."},{"level":1,"question":"What type of work permit is the spouse permit normally?","options":["Open work permit","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"It usually allows work for most employers."},{"level":1,"question":"Does a spouse OWP require an LMIA?","options":["No, it is generally LMIA-exempt when eligibility is met","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The category relies on an exemption rather than a labour market test."},{"level":1,"question":"Can a spouse OWP holder work for any employer without limits?","options":["Most employers, subject to printed conditions and restricted sectors","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Open permits still include conditions such as medical restrictions."},{"level":1,"question":"What is a dependent child in immigration terms?","options":["A child meeting IRCC age and dependency rules","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Dependent-child status is defined by regulation and policy."},{"level":1,"question":"Why is the principal applicant''s status important?","options":["It is the basis for the spouse''s eligibility","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"If the principal does not qualify, the spouse application may fail."},{"level":1,"question":"What does OWP stand for?","options":["Open Work Permit","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"OWP is the abbreviation for open work permit."},{"level":1,"question":"Is a job offer usually required for a spouse OWP?","options":["No, not usually","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explana