und","severity":"Common"},{"title":"DS-160 inconsistencies","description":"Dates, employment, or travel history mismatch with documents or prior applications.","fix":"Cross-check DS-160 against passport, I-20, and resume before submit","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Previous refusals not addressed","description":"Prior US or other country refusals hidden or unchanged circumstances.","fix":"Disclose honestly; explain what changed—stronger funds, clearer plan","severity":"High"},{"title":"Over-rehearsed or argumentative interview","description":"Client memorises script or argues with officer.","fix":"Mock interview with natural answers; listen and respond briefly","severity":"Medium"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee F-1 approval?","a":"No. Consular officers decide at interview. We prepare the file and coach for interview but never promise approval."},{"q":"How much funds to show?","a":"Typically tuition + living per I-20 for first year. Verify amount on I-20 financial page; include credible sponsor or loan evidence."},{"q":"What is 214(b)?","a":"Immigration law presumes immigrant intent. F-1 applicants must convince officer they will return after studies—ties, funds, and credible study plan matter."},{"q":"Can spouse accompany on F-2?","a":"F-2 dependants may apply separately. F-2 cannot work. Assess funds for entire family."},{"q":"When to pay SEVIS fee?","a":"Before interview, at least 3 days prior recommended. Bring I-901 receipt to embassy."},{"q":"How soon can client enter USA?","a":"No earlier than 30 days before I-20 program start date on valid F-1 visa."},{"q":"What if refused under 214(b)?","a":"No appeal. Reapply when circumstances materially improve—stronger ties, different program, or better funds."},{"q":"Is interview mandatory for renewals?","a":"Most Indian applicants attend interview. Check embassy guidance for specific renewal rules."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"F-1 non-immigrant visa for full-time academic study at a US institution certified by SEVP. Requires valid I-20, SEVIS payment, DS-160, and consular interview."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Valid I-20 from SEVP school · Proof of funds · English readiness · Non-immigrant intent · Clean immigration history"},{"q":"What is Interview focus for this service?","a":"Consular officer assesses genuine student intent, funds, and ties to India. Short, clear answers work better than memorised scripts."},{"q":"Important note on Interview focus?","a":"Consular officer assesses genuine student intent, funds, and ties to India. Short, clear answers work better than memorised scripts."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"US Department of State (embassy/consulate) · SEVIS/ICE for I-901"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"F-1 visa foil in passport; enter US no earlier than 30 days before I-20 start. Maintain full-time enrollment and SEVIS compliance."},{"q":"Is Form I-20 from SEVP-certified school required?","a":"Program and start date must be realistic"},{"q":"Is SEVIS I-901 fee paid required?","a":"Receipt required for interview"},{"q":"Is DS-160 completed accurately required?","a":"Must match I-20 and documents"},{"q":"Is Proof of financial support required?","a":"Covers tuition + living for at least first year"},{"q":"Is English proficiency (as required by school) required?","a":"TOEFL/IELTS/Duolingo per I-20"},{"q":"Is Non-immigrant intent / ties to India required?","a":"Critical for 214(b) interview"},{"q":"Is No prior visa fraud or serious inadmissibility required?","a":"No prior visa fraud or serious inadmissibility is typically required."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"2–8w — Post-interview; slot wait extra"},{"q":"What is the Government fee?","a":"USD $535 — MRV $185 + SEVIS $350"},{"q":"What is the Our approval rate?","a":"84% — ~70% industry benchmark"},{"q":"What is the Required docs?","a":"12 — + financial evidence"},{"q":"What is the Consultancy fee?","a":"See 