riority date matter is correct?","options":["Employment-based (EB) and family-based categories have different wait times. Indian-born applicants often face long backlogs in EB-2/EB-3—set realistic expecta…","Lawful permanent residence (green card) via employment sponsorship (EB-1/2/3/5) or family petition (I-130). Multi-step process involving PERM, I-140, priority …","Qualifying job offer/sponsor (EB) or qualifying family relationship · PERM for most EB-2/3 · Priority date current per Visa Bulletin · Medical and character cl…","Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Employment-based (EB) and family-based categories have different wait times. Indian-born applicants often face long backlogs in EB-2/EB-3—set realistic expectations."},{"level":1,"question":"USA – Green Card (Employment & Family): what is true regarding policy update?","options":["Confirm current USCIS filing fees (I-140, I-485, etc.) on uscis.gov. Green card timelines vary widely by category and country of birth.","Lawful permanent residence (green card) via employment sponsorship (EB-1/2/3/5) or family petition (I-130). Multi-step process involving PERM, I-140, priority …","Qualifying job offer/sponsor (EB) or qualifying family relationship · PERM for most EB-2/3 · Priority date current per Visa Bulletin · Medical and character cl…","Indian-born EB-2/EB-3 applicants often wait years after I-140 approval for priority date to become current. Monitor Visa Bulletin monthly."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Confirm current USCIS filing fees (I-140, I-485, etc.) on uscis.gov. Green card timelines vary widely by category and country of birth."},{"level":2,"question":"In the USA – Green Card (Employment & Family) process, what is the correct approach to client question: Can we guarantee green card?","options":["No. Multi-step process with DOL, USCIS, and visa availability. Neve